<Challenge Title="Challenge Area of a Circle">
    <Text>
        In this challenge, you will write a progarm to calculate the area of a circle.
        The area of a circle can be calculated by multiplying its pi by its radius squared.
    </Text>
    <TaskList Name="Area of a Circle">
        <TaskItem Name="Create a New Project">Create a new Folder called "Circle Analyzer"</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Open Folder">Open the Folder in VS Code</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Open an Integrated Terminal">Open an Integrated Terminal</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Create a new C# Project">Create a new C# Project</TaskItem>
    </TaskList>

    <Text>Create a program that does the following:</Text>
    
    <TaskItem Name="Display">Displays "I can analyze a circle!"</TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Prompt">Prompts the user "Enter the circles diameter:"</TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Float diameter">Creates a <Code>float</Code> variable called <Code>diameter</Code></TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Parse Float">Calls <Code>float.Parse(Console.ReadLine())</Code> and stores the result in the <Code>diameter</Code> variable</TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Float Radius">Create another <Code>float</Code> called <Code>radius</Code></TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Store the result">Stores the result of <Code>diameter / 2F</Code>in the <Code>radius</Code></TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Float Pi">Create a third <Code>float</Code> called <Code>pi</Code></TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Store Pi">Store the value 3.14159265359F in the <Code>pi</Code> variable.</TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Float Area">Create a third <Code>float</Code> called <Code>area</Code></TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Store Area">Stores the result of <Code>pi * radius * radius</Code> in the variable area</TaskItem>
    <TaskItem Name="Display Area">Finally, display <Code>$"The area of the circle is {area}"</Code></TaskItem>

</Challenge>